author: Wintergatan
description:
Building Marble Machine 3 - Episode 1 So it begins :)

The first parts for Marble Machine 3 are here and I've learned so much. 
The first Metal Hub for the 1200 mm double helical plywood gear is here. I am learning the value of reading instructions and trying to see if I can assemble tapered bushings correctly.
Looks like world tour is back on the menu! 

Big thanks to Alex Brem from “Brem Precision” for machining this beautiful part
Check out: https://bremprecision.nl/

Thank you to the wonderful “Ateljé Örnsberg” for the help with the BIG plywood gear. More on this in an upcoming video. Check them out here:
https://www.ateljeornsberg.se/
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/ateljeornsberg/?hl=sv

And huge thanks to everyone in the metal hub discord channel for all the input on the design and drawings.

Looking forward to continue collaborating with you all on this project 🌱

title: The first REAL parts for Marble Machine 3 are here!
